ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 min-w-0"><div class="min-w-0 pl-2 py-1.5"><div class="flex items-center gap-2"><button class="group/status flex items-center gap-2 py-1 text-sm transition-colors cursor-pointer text-left text-text-500 hover:text-text-300 flex-1 min-w-0" aria-expanded="false"><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 min-w-0" style="opacity: 1;"><span class="truncate text-sm font-base">Reading frontend design skill</span><span class="inline-flex transition-transform duration-200 shrink-0 -rotate-90"><div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">Reading frontend design skill</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div class="ease-out transition-all flex flex-col font-ui leading-normal my-3 min-h-[2.625rem] overflow-hidden border-0.5  border-border-300 rounded-lg hover:bg-bg-200 mt-3 mb-2" style="opacity: 1;"><div class="group/row flex flex-row items-center justify-between gap-4 rounded-lg text-text-300 h-[2.625rem] py-2 px-3 cursor-default"><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-2 min-w-0"><div class="w-5 h-5 flex items-center justify-center text-text-100"><div class="shrink-0 bg-bg-000 border-border-300 border-0.5 shadow-sm flex items-center justify-center !border-0 !shadow-none !bg-transparent" style="width: 16px; height: 16px; border-radius: 4.32px;"><div class="shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center bg-bg-000 text-text-300 font-medium border-0.5 border-border-300 shadow-[0_0.8px_1.6px_0_hsl(var(--always-black)/5%)]" style="width: 16px; height: 16px; font-size: 10.4px; border-radius: 4.8px;"><p class="font-ui shrink-0 leading-tight">V</p></div></div></div><div class="flex gap-2 relative bottom-[0.5px] font-base text-left leading-tight overflow-hidden overflow-ellipsis whitespace-nowrap flex-grow text-text-300">Connecting to visualize...</div></div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-1.5 min-w-0 shrink-0"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Here's the working demo. Here's how it all fits together:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The three segments</strong> auto-advance focus as you type — day fills at 2 digits, month fills at 3 letters, year at 4 digits. On iOS this naturally triggers the correct keyboard (numeric → alpha → numeric). Desktop Chrome validates with <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">pattern</code> on submit.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Chip history</strong> is stored in <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">localStorage</code>. Each submitted date appears as a tappable chip — tap the label to instantly populate all three fields, tap the ✕ to remove a specific entry. Up to 8 entries are kept.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Validation</strong> checks digit ranges, valid 3-letter month abbreviations (JAN–DEC), and sensible year bounds before accepting a submission.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">A few things to note if you take this further:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">autocapitalize="characters"</code> attribute (not shown here but easy to add) forces iOS to uppercase the month field automatically</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The history chips survive page refreshes via <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">localStorage</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You can pre-seed the chip history with common or recently used values from your backend instead of relying purely on client-side storage</li>
</ul></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
