<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Name</strong> — letters, spaces, hyphens and apostrophes only (<code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">autocapitalize="words"</code> on iOS). Single box.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Date of birth</strong> — same split DD-MMM-YYYY as before with auto-advance and chip history.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Address</strong> — letters, numbers, spaces and common punctuation. Single box.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Postal code</strong> — 6 individual single-character boxes in <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">A N A · N A N</code> layout. Alpha boxes switch to letter keyboard, digit boxes switch to numeric. Auto-advances through all 6 positions.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>RAMQ</strong> — split into <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">AAAA</code> (4 letters) and <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">NNNNNNNN</code> (8 digits). The space between them is visual only — the two segments auto-advance and store as <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">AAAA NNNNNNNN</code>.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Each field has its own chip history stored independently in <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">localStorage</code>, so tapping a chip only fills that one field, leaving the others untouched. All 5 chip stores are updated on a successful submit.</p></div></div><div class="flex flex-col gap-2 py-2"><div class="group/artifact-block relative flex text-left font-ui rounded-lg overflow-hidden border-0.5 transition duration-300 w-full hover:bg-bg-000/50 px-4 border-border-300/15 hover:border-border-200"><button type="button" class="absolute inset-0 cursor-pointer rounded-[inherit] focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-inset focus-visible:ring-accent-200" aria-label="Registration form. Open artifact."></button><div class="artifact-block-cell flex flex-1 align-start justify-between w-full"><div class="flex flex-1 gap-2 min-w-0"><div class="flex items-end w-[68px] relative shrink-0 pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true"><div class="absolute right-2 flex flex-1 overflow-hidden w-[52px] h-[71px] rounded-t-lg border-0.5 border-border-200 select-none scale-[1] group-hover/artifact-block:scale-[1.035] -rotate-[0.1rad] group-hover/artifact-block:-rotate-[0.065rad] duration-300 ease-out group-hover/artifact-block:duration-400 group-hover/artifact-block:ease-[cubic-bezier(0,0.9,0.5,1.35)] transition-transform backface-hidden will-change-transform translate-y-[19%] bg-gradient-to-b from-bg-000 to-bg-000/0 pt-4 items-start justify-center h-full"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 256 256" class="text-text-500"><path d="M67.84,92.61,25.37,128l42.47,35.39a6,6,0,1,1-7.68,9.22l-48-40a6,6,0,0,1,0-9.22l48-40a6,6,0,0,1,7.68,9.22Zm176,30.78-48-40a6,6,0,1,0-7.68,9.22L230.63,128l-42.47,35.39a6,6,0,1,0,7.68,9.22l48-40a6,6,