<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The renderer reads that definition and builds all the HTML, wiring, validation, and chip history automatically — you never touch the form code again, just the definition.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What each <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">type</code> would mean:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">alpha-full</code> — single wide text box, letters only</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">free-full</code> — single wide text box, any characters</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">split</code> — segmented input driven by a pattern string where <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">N</code>=numeric, <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">A</code>=alpha, <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">M</code>=month abbreviation, spaces and hyphens are visual separators</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">address</code> — special two-row layout with number + street + optional unit</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">dropdown</code> — select element with a named option set</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This approach means you could define a completely different form — say, a vehicle registration or an insurance claim — just by changing the JSON, with zero code changes.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Want me to build it? I'd suggest the definition lives at the top of the file as a plain JavaScript array, clearly separated from the engine below it, so it's easy to find and edit.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
