ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's the right thing to tackle first. The good news is that uploading directly to GitHub is actually <strong>easier</strong> than copy/paste once you know the steps.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Here's the basic workflow:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>On GitHub.com (no software needed):</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to your repository</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Add file → Upload files</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Drag both <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> and <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">form.json</code> onto the upload area</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll down and click <strong>Commit changes</strong></li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">GitHub will automatically serve the files at your GitHub Pages URL, and since both files are in the same folder, <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> will find <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">form.json</code> automatically.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>One thing to check</strong> — make sure GitHub Pages is enabled for your repository:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to your repo <strong>Settings</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Pages</strong> in the left sidebar</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Under Source, select <strong>Deploy from a branch</strong> and choose <strong>main</strong> (or <strong>master</strong>)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Save</strong></li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Your site will then be live at <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">https://yourusername.github.io/yourreponame/</code></p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Once you've got that working, come back and we'll build the Word template workflow on top of it. That's when it gets really powerful — design in Word, upload <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">form.json</code>, live form updates automatically, <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> never touched again.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
