ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Here's the step by step:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>1. Go to your repository on GitHub.com</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>2. You'll see a list of your existing files.</strong> Look for <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> in the list and click on it.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>3. In the top right of the file view, click the pencil icon</strong> (Edit this file)... but actually don't do that — instead look for the three dots <strong>⋯</strong> menu next to the pencil, click it and choose <strong>Delete file</strong>...</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Actually, the simplest approach for replacing a file is:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">From your repository main page click <strong>Add file → Upload files</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">A drag-and-drop area appears — drag your <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> from Downloads onto it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Do the same for <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">form.json</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">GitHub will warn you that <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> already exists and will replace it — that's fine</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll down to the <strong>Commit changes</strong> section</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Leave the default message or type something like "updated form"</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click the green <strong>Commit changes</strong> button</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Wait about 30 seconds, then visit your GitHub Pages URL and you should see the live form.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">If you're not sure what your GitHub Pages URL is, go to <strong>Settings → Pages</strong> and it will show you the exact URL at the top of that page.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
