ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's correct and intentional behaviour — <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">required: false</code> means the field is <strong>optional</strong>, not <strong>hidden</strong>. It still shows on the form, but the user can leave it blank and the form will still submit successfully.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">If you want a field to be <strong>completely hidden</strong> from the form, you have two options:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 1 — Just delete the row from your table</strong>
The simplest approach. If you don't want SIN on the form at all, don't include it in the table.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 2 — Add a <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">visible</code> property to the JSON</strong>
I can update the engine to support a <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">visible</code> column in your table, so you could write:</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6"><table class="min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal"><thead class="text-left"><tr><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Field Label</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Type</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Pattern</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Required</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Visible</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Social Insurance Number</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">split</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">NNN NNN NNN</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">No</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">No</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">And the field would be completely excluded from the form.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">So to clarify the two columns:</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6"><table class="min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal"><thead class="text-left"><tr><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Column</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Required</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Field shows but can be left blank</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Visible</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Whether the field appears at all</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Would you like me to add the <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">visible</code> column support to the engine? It would mean updating <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> once more, then you'd never need to touch it again.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
