ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Yes, absolutely. This is a natural extension of the same idea — add styling properties to your Word table and I generate both <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">form.json</code> and a <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">theme.json</code> file that the engine reads for visual settings.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The engine already reads one external file (<code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">form.json</code>), it could just as easily read a second one (<code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">theme.json</code>) for appearance.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What you could control from your Word doc:</strong></p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6"><table class="min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal"><thead class="text-left"><tr><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Property</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Examples</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Colours</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Background, card, button, field borders, text</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Font</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Family, size, weight</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Logo / image</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">URL or filename of an image to show at the top</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Card shape</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Rounded corners amount</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Button label</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">"Submit", "Register", "Send"</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Button colour</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Any colour</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Layout width</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Narrow, normal, wide</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><strong>Dark mode</strong></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">On, off, or auto (follows OS setting)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Your Word doc would get a second table</strong>, something like:</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6"><table class="min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal"><thead class="text-left"><tr><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Property</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Value</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Background colour</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem] inline-flex items-center h-5"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 border-[0.5px] border-border-200 rounded flex-shrink-0 shadow-sm mr-1 align-middle" style="background-color: rgb(240, 244, 255);"></span>#f0f4ff</code></td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Card colour</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">white</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Button colour</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem] inline-flex items-center h-5"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 border-[0.5px] border-border-200 rounded flex-shrink-0 shadow-sm mr-1 align-middle" style="background-color: rgb(42, 106, 222);"></span>#2a6ade</code></td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Font</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Georgia</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Logo</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">logo.png</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Corner radius</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">large</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
