</span></span><span># 44 44 44  ← equal amounts of red, green, blue = grey
</span><span># ff 00 00  ← full red, no green, no blue = bright red
</span><span># 00 00 ff  ← no red, no green, full blue = bright blue</span></code></pre></div></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The scale goes from <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">00</code> (none) to <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">ff</code> (full).</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>But you don't need to know any of this.</strong> Just use colour names or pick codes from a colour picker:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Easiest option — Google colour picker:</strong>
Type <strong>"colour picker"</strong> into Google and a visual picker appears right in the search results. Click the colour you want and Google shows you the hex code to copy.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Or just use names like:</strong></p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6"><table class="min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal"><thead class="text-left"><tr><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Name</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">What it looks like</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">navy</code></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Dark blue</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">steelblue</code></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Medium blue</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">crimson</code></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Deep red</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">forestgreen</code></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Dark green</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">darkorange</code></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Orange</td></tr><t