ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Unfortunately no — GitHub itself just shows you code and files, it doesn't render web pages. You always need to go to the separate GitHub Pages URL to see the live form.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">However you can make it <strong>much quicker</strong> to switch between them:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 1 — Pin both tabs</strong>
Right-click each tab in Chrome/Safari and choose <strong>Pin Tab</strong> — they shrink to small icons on the left and are always one click away.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 2 — Bookmark the Pages URL</strong>
Add your GitHub Pages URL to your bookmarks bar so it's always one click away.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 3 — GitHub has a shortcut link</strong>
In your repository, click <strong>Settings → Pages</strong> and GitHub shows your live URL right there with a <strong>Visit site</strong> button.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 4 — Split screen on Mac</strong>
Hold the green fullscreen button on your GitHub window and tile it to one side, then put your Pages tab on the other side. Both visible at once.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The typical workflow most people settle into is:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Make changes on GitHub</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Commit</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Wait ~30 seconds</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Hit <strong>⌘ R</strong> to refresh the Pages tab</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">After a few times it becomes very natural.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
