ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Good question. There are two ways to approach this:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 1 — Make the card wider</strong>
In <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">theme.json</code> just increase <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">cardWidth</code>. The default is <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">480</code> — try <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">700</code> or <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">800</code> and the form gets wider without changing the field layout.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 2 — Put fields side by side</strong>
Add a <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">row</code> grouping to <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">form.json</code> so you can specify which fields share a line. The table would get a new column:</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto w-full px-2 mb-6"><table class="min-w-full border-collapse text-sm leading-[1.7] whitespace-normal"><thead class="text-left"><tr><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Field Label</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Type</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Pattern</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Required</th><th scope="col" class="text-text-100 border-b-0.5 border-border-300/60 py-2 pr-4 align-top font-bold">Row</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">First name</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">alpha-full</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Yes</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">1</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Last name</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">alpha-full</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Yes</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">1</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Date of birth</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">split</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">NN-MMM-NNNN</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Yes</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">2</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">City &amp; province</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">city-province</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top"></td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">Yes</td><td class="border-b-0.5 border-border-300/30 py-2 pr-4 align-top">3</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Fields sharing the same row number appear side by side. Fields with unique row numbers take the full width as normal.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Both options combined</strong> works best — a wider card with some fields paired side by side looks very clean and professional.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This would require a small update to <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> to support the <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">row</code> grouping. Want me to:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Just update <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">theme.json</code> with a wider card for now, or</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Build the full side-by-side field support into <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code>?</li>
</ol></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
