or Angular application). The actual form fields are built dynamically by JavaScript after the page loads, so when I fetch the raw HTML there's nothing there yet — just an empty shell.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This is very common with modern web apps and means I can't read the fields automatically.</p>
