ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's a <strong>browser cache</strong> problem — your desktop Chrome is stubbornly holding onto the old version of <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">form.json</code>. Your phone loaded it fresh because it had no cached version.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Try these in order until it works:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>1. Hard refresh</strong>
Press <strong>⌘ Shift R</strong> in Chrome — forces a full reload ignoring cache.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>2. Open in a private/incognito window</strong>
Press <strong>⌘ Shift N</strong> to open an incognito window, then paste your GitHub Pages URL. Incognito has no cache so it always loads fresh.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>3. Clear the cache for just that site</strong>
In Chrome, click the <strong>lock icon</strong> (or ⓘ) in the address bar → <strong>Site settings</strong> → <strong>Clear data</strong>. Then refresh.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>4. Wait a few minutes</strong>
GitHub Pages has its own cache layer (CDN) that can take 2–5 minutes to propagate a new file even after you see it updated in the repository. If you just uploaded, it may simply not have reached your desktop yet.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The fact that it works perfectly on your phone confirms the new <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">form.json</code> is correct — it's purely a caching issue on the desktop side.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
