ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Yes! Looking at the screenshot the ClicSanté form has a distinct clean style:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">White background, no coloured page background</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Very light grey thin-border fields, full width</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Fields are tall with generous padding</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Labels are inside the field (placeholder style) not above it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">A clean light blue/teal accent colour</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">No card shadow — the form just sits flat on the page</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">A subtle yellow/orange banner at the very top</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">I can replicate most of that through a combination of <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">theme.json</code> updates and a small update to <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> to support <strong>inline labels</strong> (placeholder-style labels inside the field instead of above it).</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Here's what I can do from <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">theme.json</code> alone right now</strong> — no <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> changes needed:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">White page background</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Full width card</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Light grey borders</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Blue accent colour matching ClicSanté</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Georgia → back to a clean sans-serif font</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What would need a small <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> update:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Labels inside the fields (floating label style)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The top colour banner</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Want me to start with just the <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">theme.json</code> changes to get the colours and layout close, then tackle the floating labels as a second step? Or shall I do both at once?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
