ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The next step is <strong>floating labels</strong> — where the label lives inside the field as a placeholder, then floats up small when you tap the field or start typing, exactly like ClicSanté.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This requires an update to <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> because it's a behaviour change, not just a style change. The way it works:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Field appears with label sitting inside it in grey (like a placeholder)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">User taps the field → label animates up to the top of the field, small</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">User types → label stays up, text appears below it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Field is empty and unfocused → label drops back down</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">It's a well-known CSS/JS pattern called a <strong>floating label</strong> or <strong>material label</strong>.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Here's what I'll need to change in <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code>:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Wrap each input in a <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">div</code> with the label inside it (not above it as it is now)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Add CSS for the float animation</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Add a small JS check to keep the label up when a field has a value (e.g. when populated from a chip)</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">It's a contained change — all the validation, chip history, and JSON-driven field building stays exactly the same.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Shall I go ahead and build it?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
